  "instructions": [
    "mix together cornmeal, flour, warm water, sumac, salt, and black pepper in a bowl. cover and let rest for 30 minutes. heat a non-stick skillet over medium heat. brush with olive oil. cook for 2-3 minutes on each side or until crispy. mix together chopped parsley and scallions. spread sour yogurt on a plate. add cooked cornmeal mixture on top. sprinkle with parsley and scallion mixture. serve immediately."
